+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0136u41k8riu3eMkmttAZCdo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014ynBGWHztGZwBNHTbbXxei","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-collab-editor.md","content":"# Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a real-time collaborative document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, Operational Transform conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Express HTTP server with `ws` WebSocket server sharing the same HTTP server. Each document has an in-memory `DocumentRoom` that tracks connected clients and the current server version for OT transforms. SQLite (better-sqlite3) persists documents and version history. The `createApp` factory returns `{ app, start, stop }`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express 4, ws 8, better-sqlite3 11, Vitest for tests, ESLint\n\n---\n\n## File Map\n\n```\nsrc/\n  db.ts          - Database connection + schema initialization\n  ot.ts          - Operational Transform types + transform function\n  documents.ts   - Document CRUD repository (wraps DB)\n  room.ts        - DocumentRoom: in-memory session state per document\n  routes.ts      - Express REST routes\n  server.ts      - createApp factory (HTTP + WebSocket wiring)\n  tests/\n    ot.test.ts         - OT transform logic\n    documents.test.ts  - DB repository\n    routes.test.ts     - REST API integration tests\n    collab.test.ts     - WebSocket collaboration + concurrency tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/db.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\nimport { dirname, join } from 'path';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function openDb(filePath: string = ':memory:') {\n  const db = new Database(filePath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport type Db = ReturnType<typeof openDb>;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/db.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add database layer with schema initialization\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Operational Transform (`src/ot.ts`)\n\nOT for plain text: two concurrent operations on the same document version must be transformed so both apply correctly.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/ot.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests (`src/tests/ot.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { applyOp, transformOp, type TextOp } from '../ot.js';\n\ndescribe('applyOp', () => {\n  it('inserts text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' }))\n      .toBe('hello world');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello world', { type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 6 }))\n      .toBe('hello');\n  });\n\n  it('clamps insert pos to valid range', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hi', { type: 'insert', pos: 100, text: '!' }))\n      .toBe('hi!');\n  });\n\n  it('clamps delete length to available text', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hi', { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 100 }))\n      .toBe('h');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - concurrent inserts', () => {\n  it('transforms second insert when first inserts before it', () => {\n    // doc = \"ac\", version 0\n    // op1 (client A): insert 'b' at 1 => \"abc\"\n    // op2 (client B): insert 'd' at 2 => \"acd\"\n    // after applying op1 first, op2 must shift right\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 1, text: 'b' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'd' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // op1 inserted 1 char before pos 2, so op2 shifts to 3\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'd' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms second insert when first inserts after it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'xyz' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'ab' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // op1 is after op2, no shift needed\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'ab' });\n  });\n\n  it('concurrent inserts at same position: op2 shifts right', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'A' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'B' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'B' });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - concurrent deletes', () => {\n  it('transforms second delete when first deletes before it', () => {\n    // doc = \"abcdef\"\n    // op1: delete 2 chars at pos 1 => \"acdef\" -> wait, \"a\" + \"cdef\" = \"acdef\"\n    // actually op1 deletes 'bc', op2 deletes 'de' at pos 3\n    // after op1, 'de' is now at pos 1: \"a\" + \"de\" + \"f\" = \"adef\" -> pos 1\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 2 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 3, length: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 2 });\n  });\n\n  it('adjusts delete length when ops overlap', () => {\n    // doc = \"abcde\"\n    // op1: delete 3 at pos 1 => deletes 'bcd'\n    // op2: delete 2 at pos 2 => tries to delete 'cd', but op1 already deleted them\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 3 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // entire op2 range is covered by op1; nothing left to delete\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 0 });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - insert vs delete', () => {\n  it('shifts insert right when delete is before it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 3 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'x' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'x' });\n  });\n\n  it('shifts delete right when insert is before it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'abc' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 1 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 1 });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/ot.test.ts 2>&1 | head -30\n```\nExpected: FAIL - cannot find module `../ot.js`\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/ot.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport type TextOp =\n  | { type: 'insert'; pos: number; text: string }\n  | { type: 'delete'; pos: number; length: number };\n\nexport function applyOp(doc: string, op: TextOp): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.pos), doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + op.text + doc.slice(pos);\n  } else {\n    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.pos), doc.length);\n    const end = Math.min(pos + op.length, doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + doc.slice(end);\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Transform op2 against op1, so that op2 can be applied after op1.\n * Both ops were produced concurrently against the same document version.\n */\nexport function transformOp(op2: TextOp, op1: TextOp): TextOp {\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    // If op1 inserts at or before op2's position, shift op2 right\n    if (op1.pos <= op2.pos) {\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    return op2;\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    const op1End = op1.pos + op1.length;\n    const op2End = op2.pos + op2.length;\n\n    if (op1End <= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 entirely before op2: shift op2 left\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos - op1.length };\n    }\n    if (op1.pos >= op2End) {\n      // op1 entirely after op2: no change\n      return op2;\n    }\n    // Overlapping: trim op2 to only delete what op1 didn't\n    const newPos = Math.min(op2.pos, op1.pos);\n    const overlapStart = Math.max(op2.pos, op1.pos);\n    const overlapEnd = Math.min(op2End, op1End);\n    const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n    const newLength = op2.length - overlap - Math.max(0, op1.pos - op2.pos > 0 ? 0 : 0);\n    // Recalculate: chars before op1 in op2's range survive, chars inside op1 don't\n    const survivingBefore = Math.max(0, op1.pos - op2.pos);\n    const survivingAfter = Math.max(0, op2End - op1End);\n    return { type: 'delete', pos: newPos, length: survivingBefore + survivingAfter };\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    // op1 inserts before op2's range: shift op2 right\n    if (op1.pos <= op2.pos) {\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    // op1 inserts inside op2's range: expand op2's length\n    if (op1.pos < op2.pos + op2.length) {\n      return { ...op2, length: op2.length + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    return op2;\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    const op1End = op1.pos + op1.length;\n    if (op1End <= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 entirely before op2: shift op2 left\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos - op1.length };\n    }\n    if (op1.pos >= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 after op2: no change\n      return op2;\n    }\n    // op1 covers op2's position: anchor to op1.pos\n    return { ...op2, pos: op1.pos };\n  }\n\n  return op2;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ot.ts src/tests/ot.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add operational transform with comprehensive tests\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Document Repository (`src/documents.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/documents.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/documents.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests (`src/tests/documents.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { openDb } from '../db.js';\nimport { DocumentRepository } from '../documents.js';\n\ndescribe('DocumentRepository', () => {\n  let repo: DocumentRepository;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    const db = openDb(':memory:');\n    repo = new DocumentRepository(db);\n  });\n\n  it('creates a document and retrieves it by id', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Test Doc', content: 'Hello' });\n    expect(doc.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(doc.title).toBe('Test Doc');\n    expect(doc.content).toBe('Hello');\n\n    const found = repo.findById(doc.id);\n    expect(found).toBeDefined();\n    expect(found!.title).toBe('Test Doc');\n  });\n\n  it('lists all documents', () => {\n    repo.create({ title: 'A', content: '' });\n    repo.create({ title: 'B', content: '' });\n    const all = repo.list();\n    expect(all.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('updates document title and content', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Old', content: 'old content' });\n    const updated = repo.update(doc.id, { title: 'New', content: 'new content' });\n    expect(updated).toBeDefined();\n    expect(updated!.title).toBe('New');\n    expect(updated!.content).toBe('new content');\n  });\n\n  it('returns null for non-existent document', () => {\n    expect(repo.findById('no-such-id')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a document', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Bye', content: '' });\n    const deleted = repo.delete(doc.id);\n    expect(deleted).toBe(true);\n    expect(repo.findById(doc.id)).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('saves version history on update', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Doc', content: 'v1' });\n    repo.update(doc.id, { content: 'v2' });\n    repo.update(doc.id, { content: 'v3' });\n    const history = repo.getHistory(doc.id);\n    expect(history.length).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(2);\n  });\n\n  it('applies an operation and records version', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Doc', content: 'hello' });\n    const op = { type: 'insert' as const, pos: 5, text: ' world' };\n    const updated = repo.applyOperation(doc.id, op, 0);\n    expect(updated).toBeDefined();\n    expect(updated!.content).toBe('hello world');\n    const history = repo.getHistory(doc.id);\n    expect(history.length).toBe(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run to verify fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/documents.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/documents.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport type { Db } from './db.js';\nimport { applyOp, type TextOp } from './ot.js';\n\nexport interface Document {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface DocumentVersion {\n  id: number;\n  document_id: string;\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport class DocumentRepository {\n  constructor(private db: Db) {}\n\n  create(input: { title: string; content?: string }): Document {\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content)\n      VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n    `).run(id, input.title, input.content ?? '');\n\n    // Record initial version\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content)\n      VALUES (?, 0, ?)\n    `).run(id, input.content ?? '');\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n\n  findById(id: string): Document | null {\n    const row = this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT d.id, d.title, d.content, d.created_at, d.updated_at,\n             COALESCE((SELECT MAX(v.version) FROM versions v WHERE v.document_id = d.id), 0) as version\n      FROM documents d\n      WHERE d.id = ?\n    `).get(id) as Document | undefined;\n    return row ?? null;\n  }\n\n  list(): Document[] {\n    return this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT d.id, d.title, d.content, d.created_at, d.updated_at,\n             COALESCE((SELECT MAX(v.version) FROM versions v WHERE v.document_id = d.id), 0) as version\n      FROM documents d\n      ORDER BY d.updated_at DESC\n    `).all() as Document[];\n  }\n\n  update(id: string, input: { title?: string; content?: string }): Document | null {\n    const doc = this.findById(id);\n    if (!doc) return null;\n\n    const newTitle = input.title ?? doc.title;\n    const newContent = input.content ?? doc.content;\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      UPDATE documents SET title = ?, content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now')\n      WHERE id = ?\n    `).run(newTitle, newContent, id);\n\n    if (input.content !== undefined && input.content !== doc.content) {\n      const nextVersion = doc.version + 1;\n      this.db.prepare(`\n        INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content)\n        VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n      `).run(id, nextVersion, newContent);\n    }\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n\n  delete(id: string): boolean {\n    const result = this.db.prepare('DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n    return result.changes > 0;\n  }\n\n  getHistory(id: string): DocumentVersion[] {\n    return this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT * FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?\n      ORDER BY version ASC\n    `).all(id) as DocumentVersion[];\n  }\n\n  applyOperation(id: string, op: TextOp, _clientVersion: number): Document | null {\n    const doc = this.findById(id);\n    if (!doc) return null;\n\n    const newContent = applyOp(doc.content, op);\n    const nextVersion = doc.version + 1;\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\n    `).run(newContent, id);\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation)\n      VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)\n    `).run(id, nextVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(op));\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/documents.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/documents.ts src/tests/documents.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add document repository with version history\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Document Room (in-memory collaboration state) (`src/room.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/room.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2, Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/room.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport type { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\nimport { transformOp, type TextOp } from './ot.js';\n\nexport interface ClientMessage {\n  type: 'operation';\n  clientVersion: number;\n  op: TextOp;\n}\n\nexport interface ServerMessage {\n  type: 'sync' | 'operation' | 'ack' | 'error';\n  [key: string]: unknown;\n}\n\ninterface PendingOp {\n  op: TextOp;\n  serverVersion: number;\n}\n\nexport class DocumentRoom {\n  private clients: Set<WebSocket> = new Set();\n  // Ops applied since initial version (for OT transform of late-arriving ops)\n  private opLog: PendingOp[] = [];\n  private serverVersion: number;\n\n  constructor(\n    private docId: string,\n    private repo: DocumentRepository,\n  ) {\n    const doc = this.repo.findById(docId);\n    this.serverVersion = doc?.version ?? 0;\n  }\n\n  get clientCount(): number {\n    return this.clients.size;\n  }\n\n  join(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.add(ws);\n    const doc = this.repo.findById(this.docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' });\n      ws.close();\n      return;\n    }\n    this.send(ws, {\n      type: 'sync',\n      documentId: this.docId,\n      content: doc.content,\n      version: doc.version,\n    });\n  }\n\n  leave(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.delete(ws);\n  }\n\n  handleOperation(ws: WebSocket, msg: ClientMessage): void {\n    // Validate op fields\n    if (!msg.op || !msg.op.type) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n    if (msg.op.type === 'insert' && (typeof msg.op.pos !== 'number' || typeof msg.op.text !== 'string')) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid insert operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n    if (msg.op.type === 'delete' && (typeof msg.op.pos !== 'number' || typeof msg.op.length !== 'number')) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid delete operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Transform op against all server ops since client's version\n    let op = msg.op;\n    const clientVersion = msg.clientVersion ?? this.serverVersion;\n    const opsToTransformAgainst = this.opLog.filter(\n      (p) => p.serverVersion > clientVersion,\n    );\n    for (const pending of opsToTransformAgainst) {\n      op = transformOp(op, pending.op);\n    }\n\n    // Apply to DB\n    const updated = this.repo.applyOperation(this.docId, op, this.serverVersion);\n    if (!updated) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Failed to apply operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    this.serverVersion = updated.version;\n    this.opLog.push({ op, serverVersion: this.serverVersion });\n\n    // Ack to sender\n    this.send(ws, { type: 'ack', version: this.serverVersion });\n\n    // Broadcast to others\n    const broadcast = { type: 'operation', op, version: this.serverVersion };\n    for (const client of this.clients) {\n      if (client !== ws && client.readyState === 1 /* OPEN */) {\n        this.send(client, broadcast);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private send(ws: WebSocket, msg: ServerMessage): void {\n    if (ws.readyState === 1 /* OPEN */) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify(msg));\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport class RoomManager {\n  private rooms = new Map<string, DocumentRoom>();\n\n  constructor(private repo: DocumentRepository) {}\n\n  getOrCreate(docId: string): DocumentRoom {\n    let room = this.rooms.get(docId);\n    if (!room) {\n      room = new DocumentRoom(docId, this.repo);\n      this.rooms.set(docId, room);\n    }\n    return room;\n  }\n\n  remove(docId: string): void {\n    this.rooms.delete(docId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/room.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add DocumentRoom for in-memory OT session management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: REST Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/routes.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests (`src/tests/routes.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../server.js';\n\ndescribe('REST API', () => {\n  let server: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    server = createApp(':memory:');\n    await server.start(0);\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await server.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents creates a document', async () => {\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'My Doc', content: 'Hello' })\n      .expect(201);\n\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('My Doc');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('Hello');\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents lists documents', async () => {\n    await request(server.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'A' });\n    await request(server.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'B' });\n    const res = await request(server.app).get('/documents').expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Doc' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('Doc');\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns 404 for missing doc', async () => {\n    await request(server.app).get('/documents/nonexistent').expect(404);\n  });\n\n  it('PUT /documents/:id updates a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Old', content: 'old' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .put(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .send({ title: 'New', content: 'new' })\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('New');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('new');\n  });\n\n  it('DELETE /documents/:id deletes a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Bye' });\n    await request(server.app)\n      .delete(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(204);\n    await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(404);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id/history returns version history', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'v1' });\n    await request(server.app)\n      .put(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .send({ content: 'v2' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}/history`)\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents rejects missing title', async () => {\n    await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ content: 'no title' })\n      .expect(400);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run to verify fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/routes.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/routes.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, type Request, type Response } from 'express';\nimport type { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\n\nexport function createRouter(repo: DocumentRepository): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // List all documents\n  router.get('/documents', (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    res.json(repo.list());\n  });\n\n  // Get single document\n  router.get('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = repo.findById(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Get version history\n  router.get('/documents/:id/history', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = repo.findById(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(repo.getHistory(req.params.id));\n  });\n\n  // Create document\n  router.post('/documents', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string') {\n      return res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n    }\n    const doc = repo.create({ title, content: content ?? '' });\n    return res.status(201).json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Update document\n  router.put('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    const updated = repo.update(req.params.id, { title, content });\n    if (!updated) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(updated);\n  });\n\n  // Delete document\n  router.delete('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const deleted = repo.delete(req.params.id);\n    if (!deleted) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests (will pass after server.ts is written in Task 6)**\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Server Factory (`src/server.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 3, Task 4, Task 5\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/server.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, type Server as HttpServer } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer, type WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { openDb } from './db.js';\nimport { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\nimport { RoomManager } from './room.js';\nimport { createRouter } from './routes.js';\nimport type { ClientMessage } from './room.js';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Application;\n  start(port?: number): Promise<number>;\n  stop(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath: string = ':memory:'): AppInstance {\n  const db = openDb(dbPath);\n  const repo = new DocumentRepository(db);\n  const roomManager = new RoomManager(repo);\n\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n  app.use(createRouter(repo));\n\n  const httpServer: HttpServer = createServer(app);\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n\n  // Handle WebSocket upgrade: path must be /documents/:id/ws\n  httpServer.on('upgrade', (request, socket, head) => {\n    const url = request.url ?? '';\n    const match = url.match(/^\\/documents\\/([^/]+)\\/ws$/);\n    if (!match) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n    const docId = match[1];\n    wss.handleUpgrade(request, socket, head, (ws) => {\n      wss.emit('connection', ws, docId);\n    });\n  });\n\n  wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, docId: string) => {\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = repo.findById(docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' }));\n      ws.close();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const room = roomManager.getOrCreate(docId);\n    room.join(ws);\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      let msg: unknown;\n      try {\n        msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n      } catch {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid JSON' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (typeof msg !== 'object' || msg === null || !('type' in msg)) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Missing type field' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const typed = msg as Record<string, unknown>;\n      if (typed['type'] === 'operation') {\n        room.handleOperation(ws, typed as unknown as ClientMessage);\n      } else {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Unknown message type' }));\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      room.leave(ws);\n    });\n\n    ws.on('error', (err) => {\n      console.error(`WebSocket error on doc ${docId}:`, err.message);\n      room.leave(ws);\n    });\n  });\n\n  let listening = false;\n\n  return {\n    app,\n    start(port = 0): Promise<number> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        if (listening) {\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0);\n          return;\n        }\n        httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n          listening = true;\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0);\n        });\n        httpServer.once('error', reject);\n      });\n    },\n    stop(): Promise<void> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        wss.close();\n        httpServer.close((err) => {\n          if (err) reject(err);\n          else {\n            listening = false;\n            db.close();\n            resolve();\n          }\n        });\n      });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests so far**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/routes.test.ts src/tests/documents.test.ts src/tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 3: Build check**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build 2>&1 | head -40\n```\nExpected: No errors\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/server.ts src/routes.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add Express server with WebSocket collaboration support\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: WebSocket Collaboration Tests (`src/tests/collab.test.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/collab.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Write collaboration tests**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport WebSocket from 'ws';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../server.js';\n\ntype ServerMsg = { type: string; content?: string; version?: number; op?: unknown; message?: string };\n\nfunction connect(port: number, docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/documents/${docId}/ws`);\n    ws.once('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction nextMessage(ws: WebSocket): Promise<ServerMsg> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    ws.once('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        resolve(JSON.parse(data.toString()));\n      } catch (e) {\n        reject(e);\n      }\n    });\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction closeWs(ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    if (ws.readyState === WebSocket.CLOSED) { resolve(); return; }\n    ws.once('close', resolve);\n    ws.close();\n  });\n}\n\ndescribe('WebSocket collaboration', () => {\n  let server: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n  let port: number;\n  let docId: string;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    server = createApp(':memory:');\n    port = await server.start(0);\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Collab Doc', content: 'hello' });\n    docId = res.body.id;\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await server.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('sends sync message on connect', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    const msg = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('sync');\n    expect(msg.content).toBe('hello');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('returns error for nonexistent document', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, 'nonexistent-doc');\n    const msg = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('applies an insert operation and acks', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync = await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n    expect(sync.type).toBe('sync');\n\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'operation',\n      clientVersion: sync.version,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' },\n    }));\n\n    const ack = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // Verify via REST\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('hello world');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('broadcasts operation to other clients', async () => {\n    const ws1 = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws1); // sync\n\n    const ws2 = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'operation',\n      clientVersion: 0,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' },\n    }));\n\n    const ack = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    const broadcast = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(broadcast.type).toBe('operation');\n    expect((broadcast.op as { text?: string }).text).toBe('!');\n\n    await closeWs(ws1);\n    await closeWs(ws2);\n  });\n\n  it('converges concurrent edits from two clients', async () => {\n    // Start: \"hello\"\n    // Client A inserts \" world\" at pos 5 (version 0)\n    // Client B inserts \"!\" at pos 5 (version 0) - concurrent\n    // Expected after OT: \"hello world!\" or \"hello! world\" - both preserved\n    const ws1 = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync1 = await nextMessage(ws1);\n\n    const ws2 = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync2 = await nextMessage(ws2);\n\n    // Both see version 0 \"hello\"\n    expect(sync1.version).toBe(sync2.version);\n\n    const opA = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' };\n    const opB = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' };\n\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: sync1.version, op: opA }));\n    const ackA = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(ackA.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // ws2 gets broadcast of opA\n    const broadcastA = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(broadcastA.type).toBe('operation');\n\n    // ws2 sends its op at old version - server will transform it\n    ws2.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: sync2.version, op: opB }));\n    const ackB = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(ackB.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // ws1 gets broadcast of transformed opB\n    const broadcastB = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(broadcastB.type).toBe('operation');\n\n    // Verify final content contains both edits\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    const finalContent = res.body.content as string;\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('world');\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('!');\n\n    await closeWs(ws1);\n    await closeWs(ws2);\n  });\n\n  it('rejects malformed operation (missing op fields)', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: 0, op: { type: 'insert' } }));\n    const err = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('rejects invalid JSON', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    ws.send('not-json');\n    const err = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('handles 10 concurrent clients without corruption', async () => {\n    const clients: WebSocket[] = [];\n    const N = 10;\n\n    for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n      const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n      await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n      clients.push(ws);\n    }\n\n    // Each client sends one insert\n    const sends = clients.map((ws, i) =>\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'operation',\n        clientVersion: 0,\n        op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: `${i}` },\n      }))\n    );\n\n    // Wait for all acks\n    const acks = await Promise.all(clients.map(nextMessage));\n    expect(acks.every((a) => a.type === 'ack')).toBe(true);\n\n    // Final content should contain all 10 digits\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    const content = res.body.content as string;\n    for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n      expect(content).toContain(`${i}`);\n    }\n\n    await Promise.all(clients.map(closeWs));\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nFix any lint errors found.\n\n**Step 4: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/tests/collab.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add WebSocket collaboration integration tests\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Lint Configuration Fix (if needed)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 7\n\nIf `npm run lint` fails due to missing ESLint config:\n\n**Step 1: Check for ESLint config**\n\n```bash\nls /workspace/.eslint*\n```\n\nIf no config exists, create `.eslintrc.cjs`:\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any': 'warn',\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n};\n```\n\n**Step 2: Re-run lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\n\n**Step 3: Commit if changes needed**\n\n```bash\ngit add .eslintrc.cjs\ngit commit -m \"chore: add ESLint configuration\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Final Verification\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint && npx vitest run\n```\n\nAll three must pass cleanly before the implementation is considered complete.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":195,"cache_read_input_tokens":25596,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":195},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3406903b-1314-455e-b366-1149b0691a1d","uuid":"0dd06848-b6eb-417a-9d01-a2c150a4a595"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ynBGWHztGZwBNHTbbXxei","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-collab-editor.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3406903b-1314-455e-b366-1149b0691a1d","uuid":"fb7cdd40-7c1e-4557-be26-2bafa8e38588","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-collab-editor.md","content":"# Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a real-time collaborative document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, Operational Transform conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Express HTTP server with `ws` WebSocket server sharing the same HTTP server. Each document has an in-memory `DocumentRoom` that tracks connected clients and the current server version for OT transforms. SQLite (better-sqlite3) persists documents and version history. The `createApp` factory returns `{ app, start, stop }`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express 4, ws 8, better-sqlite3 11, Vitest for tests, ESLint\n\n---\n\n## File Map\n\n```\nsrc/\n  db.ts          - Database connection + schema initialization\n  ot.ts          - Operational Transform types + transform function\n  documents.ts   - Document CRUD repository (wraps DB)\n  room.ts        - DocumentRoom: in-memory session state per document\n  routes.ts      - Express REST routes\n  server.ts      - createApp factory (HTTP + WebSocket wiring)\n  tests/\n    ot.test.ts         - OT transform logic\n    documents.test.ts  - DB repository\n    routes.test.ts     - REST API integration tests\n    collab.test.ts     - WebSocket collaboration + concurrency tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/db.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\nimport { dirname, join } from 'path';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function openDb(filePath: string = ':memory:') {\n  const db = new Database(filePath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport type Db = ReturnType<typeof openDb>;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/db.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add database layer with schema initialization\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Operational Transform (`src/ot.ts`)\n\nOT for plain text: two concurrent operations on the same document version must be transformed so both apply correctly.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/ot.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests (`src/tests/ot.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { applyOp, transformOp, type TextOp } from '../ot.js';\n\ndescribe('applyOp', () => {\n  it('inserts text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' }))\n      .toBe('hello world');\n  });\n\n  it('deletes text at position', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello world', { type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 6 }))\n      .toBe('hello');\n  });\n\n  it('clamps insert pos to valid range', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hi', { type: 'insert', pos: 100, text: '!' }))\n      .toBe('hi!');\n  });\n\n  it('clamps delete length to available text', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hi', { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 100 }))\n      .toBe('h');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - concurrent inserts', () => {\n  it('transforms second insert when first inserts before it', () => {\n    // doc = \"ac\", version 0\n    // op1 (client A): insert 'b' at 1 => \"abc\"\n    // op2 (client B): insert 'd' at 2 => \"acd\"\n    // after applying op1 first, op2 must shift right\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 1, text: 'b' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'd' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // op1 inserted 1 char before pos 2, so op2 shifts to 3\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'd' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms second insert when first inserts after it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'xyz' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'ab' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // op1 is after op2, no shift needed\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'ab' });\n  });\n\n  it('concurrent inserts at same position: op2 shifts right', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'A' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'B' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'B' });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - concurrent deletes', () => {\n  it('transforms second delete when first deletes before it', () => {\n    // doc = \"abcdef\"\n    // op1: delete 2 chars at pos 1 => \"acdef\" -> wait, \"a\" + \"cdef\" = \"acdef\"\n    // actually op1 deletes 'bc', op2 deletes 'de' at pos 3\n    // after op1, 'de' is now at pos 1: \"a\" + \"de\" + \"f\" = \"adef\" -> pos 1\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 2 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 3, length: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 2 });\n  });\n\n  it('adjusts delete length when ops overlap', () => {\n    // doc = \"abcde\"\n    // op1: delete 3 at pos 1 => deletes 'bcd'\n    // op2: delete 2 at pos 2 => tries to delete 'cd', but op1 already deleted them\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 3 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 2 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    // entire op2 range is covered by op1; nothing left to delete\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 1, length: 0 });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transformOp - insert vs delete', () => {\n  it('shifts insert right when delete is before it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 3 };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'x' };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'x' });\n  });\n\n  it('shifts delete right when insert is before it', () => {\n    const op1: TextOp = { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'abc' };\n    const op2: TextOp = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 1 };\n    const transformed = transformOp(op2, op1);\n    expect(transformed).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 1 });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/ot.test.ts 2>&1 | head -30\n```\nExpected: FAIL - cannot find module `../ot.js`\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/ot.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport type TextOp =\n  | { type: 'insert'; pos: number; text: string }\n  | { type: 'delete'; pos: number; length: number };\n\nexport function applyOp(doc: string, op: TextOp): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.pos), doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + op.text + doc.slice(pos);\n  } else {\n    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.pos), doc.length);\n    const end = Math.min(pos + op.length, doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + doc.slice(end);\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Transform op2 against op1, so that op2 can be applied after op1.\n * Both ops were produced concurrently against the same document version.\n */\nexport function transformOp(op2: TextOp, op1: TextOp): TextOp {\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    // If op1 inserts at or before op2's position, shift op2 right\n    if (op1.pos <= op2.pos) {\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    return op2;\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    const op1End = op1.pos + op1.length;\n    const op2End = op2.pos + op2.length;\n\n    if (op1End <= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 entirely before op2: shift op2 left\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos - op1.length };\n    }\n    if (op1.pos >= op2End) {\n      // op1 entirely after op2: no change\n      return op2;\n    }\n    // Overlapping: trim op2 to only delete what op1 didn't\n    const newPos = Math.min(op2.pos, op1.pos);\n    const overlapStart = Math.max(op2.pos, op1.pos);\n    const overlapEnd = Math.min(op2End, op1End);\n    const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n    const newLength = op2.length - overlap - Math.max(0, op1.pos - op2.pos > 0 ? 0 : 0);\n    // Recalculate: chars before op1 in op2's range survive, chars inside op1 don't\n    const survivingBefore = Math.max(0, op1.pos - op2.pos);\n    const survivingAfter = Math.max(0, op2End - op1End);\n    return { type: 'delete', pos: newPos, length: survivingBefore + survivingAfter };\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    // op1 inserts before op2's range: shift op2 right\n    if (op1.pos <= op2.pos) {\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    // op1 inserts inside op2's range: expand op2's length\n    if (op1.pos < op2.pos + op2.length) {\n      return { ...op2, length: op2.length + op1.text.length };\n    }\n    return op2;\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    const op1End = op1.pos + op1.length;\n    if (op1End <= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 entirely before op2: shift op2 left\n      return { ...op2, pos: op2.pos - op1.length };\n    }\n    if (op1.pos >= op2.pos) {\n      // op1 after op2: no change\n      return op2;\n    }\n    // op1 covers op2's position: anchor to op1.pos\n    return { ...op2, pos: op1.pos };\n  }\n\n  return op2;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ot.ts src/tests/ot.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add operational transform with comprehensive tests\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Document Repository (`src/documents.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/documents.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/documents.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests (`src/tests/documents.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { openDb } from '../db.js';\nimport { DocumentRepository } from '../documents.js';\n\ndescribe('DocumentRepository', () => {\n  let repo: DocumentRepository;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    const db = openDb(':memory:');\n    repo = new DocumentRepository(db);\n  });\n\n  it('creates a document and retrieves it by id', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Test Doc', content: 'Hello' });\n    expect(doc.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(doc.title).toBe('Test Doc');\n    expect(doc.content).toBe('Hello');\n\n    const found = repo.findById(doc.id);\n    expect(found).toBeDefined();\n    expect(found!.title).toBe('Test Doc');\n  });\n\n  it('lists all documents', () => {\n    repo.create({ title: 'A', content: '' });\n    repo.create({ title: 'B', content: '' });\n    const all = repo.list();\n    expect(all.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('updates document title and content', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Old', content: 'old content' });\n    const updated = repo.update(doc.id, { title: 'New', content: 'new content' });\n    expect(updated).toBeDefined();\n    expect(updated!.title).toBe('New');\n    expect(updated!.content).toBe('new content');\n  });\n\n  it('returns null for non-existent document', () => {\n    expect(repo.findById('no-such-id')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('deletes a document', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Bye', content: '' });\n    const deleted = repo.delete(doc.id);\n    expect(deleted).toBe(true);\n    expect(repo.findById(doc.id)).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('saves version history on update', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Doc', content: 'v1' });\n    repo.update(doc.id, { content: 'v2' });\n    repo.update(doc.id, { content: 'v3' });\n    const history = repo.getHistory(doc.id);\n    expect(history.length).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(2);\n  });\n\n  it('applies an operation and records version', () => {\n    const doc = repo.create({ title: 'Doc', content: 'hello' });\n    const op = { type: 'insert' as const, pos: 5, text: ' world' };\n    const updated = repo.applyOperation(doc.id, op, 0);\n    expect(updated).toBeDefined();\n    expect(updated!.content).toBe('hello world');\n    const history = repo.getHistory(doc.id);\n    expect(history.length).toBe(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run to verify fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/documents.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/documents.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport type { Db } from './db.js';\nimport { applyOp, type TextOp } from './ot.js';\n\nexport interface Document {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface DocumentVersion {\n  id: number;\n  document_id: string;\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport class DocumentRepository {\n  constructor(private db: Db) {}\n\n  create(input: { title: string; content?: string }): Document {\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content)\n      VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n    `).run(id, input.title, input.content ?? '');\n\n    // Record initial version\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content)\n      VALUES (?, 0, ?)\n    `).run(id, input.content ?? '');\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n\n  findById(id: string): Document | null {\n    const row = this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT d.id, d.title, d.content, d.created_at, d.updated_at,\n             COALESCE((SELECT MAX(v.version) FROM versions v WHERE v.document_id = d.id), 0) as version\n      FROM documents d\n      WHERE d.id = ?\n    `).get(id) as Document | undefined;\n    return row ?? null;\n  }\n\n  list(): Document[] {\n    return this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT d.id, d.title, d.content, d.created_at, d.updated_at,\n             COALESCE((SELECT MAX(v.version) FROM versions v WHERE v.document_id = d.id), 0) as version\n      FROM documents d\n      ORDER BY d.updated_at DESC\n    `).all() as Document[];\n  }\n\n  update(id: string, input: { title?: string; content?: string }): Document | null {\n    const doc = this.findById(id);\n    if (!doc) return null;\n\n    const newTitle = input.title ?? doc.title;\n    const newContent = input.content ?? doc.content;\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      UPDATE documents SET title = ?, content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now')\n      WHERE id = ?\n    `).run(newTitle, newContent, id);\n\n    if (input.content !== undefined && input.content !== doc.content) {\n      const nextVersion = doc.version + 1;\n      this.db.prepare(`\n        INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content)\n        VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n      `).run(id, nextVersion, newContent);\n    }\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n\n  delete(id: string): boolean {\n    const result = this.db.prepare('DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n    return result.changes > 0;\n  }\n\n  getHistory(id: string): DocumentVersion[] {\n    return this.db.prepare(`\n      SELECT * FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?\n      ORDER BY version ASC\n    `).all(id) as DocumentVersion[];\n  }\n\n  applyOperation(id: string, op: TextOp, _clientVersion: number): Document | null {\n    const doc = this.findById(id);\n    if (!doc) return null;\n\n    const newContent = applyOp(doc.content, op);\n    const nextVersion = doc.version + 1;\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\n    `).run(newContent, id);\n\n    this.db.prepare(`\n      INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation)\n      VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)\n    `).run(id, nextVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(op));\n\n    return this.findById(id)!;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/documents.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/documents.ts src/tests/documents.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add document repository with version history\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Document Room (in-memory collaboration state) (`src/room.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/room.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2, Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/room.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport type { WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport type { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\nimport { transformOp, type TextOp } from './ot.js';\n\nexport interface ClientMessage {\n  type: 'operation';\n  clientVersion: number;\n  op: TextOp;\n}\n\nexport interface ServerMessage {\n  type: 'sync' | 'operation' | 'ack' | 'error';\n  [key: string]: unknown;\n}\n\ninterface PendingOp {\n  op: TextOp;\n  serverVersion: number;\n}\n\nexport class DocumentRoom {\n  private clients: Set<WebSocket> = new Set();\n  // Ops applied since initial version (for OT transform of late-arriving ops)\n  private opLog: PendingOp[] = [];\n  private serverVersion: number;\n\n  constructor(\n    private docId: string,\n    private repo: DocumentRepository,\n  ) {\n    const doc = this.repo.findById(docId);\n    this.serverVersion = doc?.version ?? 0;\n  }\n\n  get clientCount(): number {\n    return this.clients.size;\n  }\n\n  join(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.add(ws);\n    const doc = this.repo.findById(this.docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' });\n      ws.close();\n      return;\n    }\n    this.send(ws, {\n      type: 'sync',\n      documentId: this.docId,\n      content: doc.content,\n      version: doc.version,\n    });\n  }\n\n  leave(ws: WebSocket): void {\n    this.clients.delete(ws);\n  }\n\n  handleOperation(ws: WebSocket, msg: ClientMessage): void {\n    // Validate op fields\n    if (!msg.op || !msg.op.type) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n    if (msg.op.type === 'insert' && (typeof msg.op.pos !== 'number' || typeof msg.op.text !== 'string')) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid insert operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n    if (msg.op.type === 'delete' && (typeof msg.op.pos !== 'number' || typeof msg.op.length !== 'number')) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid delete operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Transform op against all server ops since client's version\n    let op = msg.op;\n    const clientVersion = msg.clientVersion ?? this.serverVersion;\n    const opsToTransformAgainst = this.opLog.filter(\n      (p) => p.serverVersion > clientVersion,\n    );\n    for (const pending of opsToTransformAgainst) {\n      op = transformOp(op, pending.op);\n    }\n\n    // Apply to DB\n    const updated = this.repo.applyOperation(this.docId, op, this.serverVersion);\n    if (!updated) {\n      this.send(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Failed to apply operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    this.serverVersion = updated.version;\n    this.opLog.push({ op, serverVersion: this.serverVersion });\n\n    // Ack to sender\n    this.send(ws, { type: 'ack', version: this.serverVersion });\n\n    // Broadcast to others\n    const broadcast = { type: 'operation', op, version: this.serverVersion };\n    for (const client of this.clients) {\n      if (client !== ws && client.readyState === 1 /* OPEN */) {\n        this.send(client, broadcast);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private send(ws: WebSocket, msg: ServerMessage): void {\n    if (ws.readyState === 1 /* OPEN */) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify(msg));\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport class RoomManager {\n  private rooms = new Map<string, DocumentRoom>();\n\n  constructor(private repo: DocumentRepository) {}\n\n  getOrCreate(docId: string): DocumentRoom {\n    let room = this.rooms.get(docId);\n    if (!room) {\n      room = new DocumentRoom(docId, this.repo);\n      this.rooms.set(docId, room);\n    }\n    return room;\n  }\n\n  remove(docId: string): void {\n    this.rooms.delete(docId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/room.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add DocumentRoom for in-memory OT session management\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: REST Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/routes.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests (`src/tests/routes.test.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../server.js';\n\ndescribe('REST API', () => {\n  let server: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    server = createApp(':memory:');\n    await server.start(0);\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await server.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents creates a document', async () => {\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'My Doc', content: 'Hello' })\n      .expect(201);\n\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('My Doc');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('Hello');\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents lists documents', async () => {\n    await request(server.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'A' });\n    await request(server.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'B' });\n    const res = await request(server.app).get('/documents').expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Doc' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('Doc');\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id returns 404 for missing doc', async () => {\n    await request(server.app).get('/documents/nonexistent').expect(404);\n  });\n\n  it('PUT /documents/:id updates a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Old', content: 'old' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .put(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .send({ title: 'New', content: 'new' })\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('New');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('new');\n  });\n\n  it('DELETE /documents/:id deletes a document', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Bye' });\n    await request(server.app)\n      .delete(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(204);\n    await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .expect(404);\n  });\n\n  it('GET /documents/:id/history returns version history', async () => {\n    const create = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'v1' });\n    await request(server.app)\n      .put(`/documents/${create.body.id}`)\n      .send({ content: 'v2' });\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .get(`/documents/${create.body.id}/history`)\n      .expect(200);\n    expect(res.body.length).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);\n  });\n\n  it('POST /documents rejects missing title', async () => {\n    await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ content: 'no title' })\n      .expect(400);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run to verify fail**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/routes.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write `src/routes.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, type Request, type Response } from 'express';\nimport type { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\n\nexport function createRouter(repo: DocumentRepository): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // List all documents\n  router.get('/documents', (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    res.json(repo.list());\n  });\n\n  // Get single document\n  router.get('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = repo.findById(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Get version history\n  router.get('/documents/:id/history', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = repo.findById(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(repo.getHistory(req.params.id));\n  });\n\n  // Create document\n  router.post('/documents', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string') {\n      return res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n    }\n    const doc = repo.create({ title, content: content ?? '' });\n    return res.status(201).json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Update document\n  router.put('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    const updated = repo.update(req.params.id, { title, content });\n    if (!updated) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.json(updated);\n  });\n\n  // Delete document\n  router.delete('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const deleted = repo.delete(req.params.id);\n    if (!deleted) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });\n    return res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests (will pass after server.ts is written in Task 6)**\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Server Factory (`src/server.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1, Task 3, Task 4, Task 5\n\n**Step 1: Write `src/server.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, type Server as HttpServer } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer, type WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { openDb } from './db.js';\nimport { DocumentRepository } from './documents.js';\nimport { RoomManager } from './room.js';\nimport { createRouter } from './routes.js';\nimport type { ClientMessage } from './room.js';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Application;\n  start(port?: number): Promise<number>;\n  stop(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath: string = ':memory:'): AppInstance {\n  const db = openDb(dbPath);\n  const repo = new DocumentRepository(db);\n  const roomManager = new RoomManager(repo);\n\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n  app.use(createRouter(repo));\n\n  const httpServer: HttpServer = createServer(app);\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n\n  // Handle WebSocket upgrade: path must be /documents/:id/ws\n  httpServer.on('upgrade', (request, socket, head) => {\n    const url = request.url ?? '';\n    const match = url.match(/^\\/documents\\/([^/]+)\\/ws$/);\n    if (!match) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n    const docId = match[1];\n    wss.handleUpgrade(request, socket, head, (ws) => {\n      wss.emit('connection', ws, docId);\n    });\n  });\n\n  wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, docId: string) => {\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = repo.findById(docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' }));\n      ws.close();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const room = roomManager.getOrCreate(docId);\n    room.join(ws);\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      let msg: unknown;\n      try {\n        msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n      } catch {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid JSON' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (typeof msg !== 'object' || msg === null || !('type' in msg)) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Missing type field' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const typed = msg as Record<string, unknown>;\n      if (typed['type'] === 'operation') {\n        room.handleOperation(ws, typed as unknown as ClientMessage);\n      } else {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Unknown message type' }));\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      room.leave(ws);\n    });\n\n    ws.on('error', (err) => {\n      console.error(`WebSocket error on doc ${docId}:`, err.message);\n      room.leave(ws);\n    });\n  });\n\n  let listening = false;\n\n  return {\n    app,\n    start(port = 0): Promise<number> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        if (listening) {\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0);\n          return;\n        }\n        httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n          listening = true;\n          const addr = httpServer.address();\n          resolve(typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0);\n        });\n        httpServer.once('error', reject);\n      });\n    },\n    stop(): Promise<void> {\n      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        wss.close();\n        httpServer.close((err) => {\n          if (err) reject(err);\n          else {\n            listening = false;\n            db.close();\n            resolve();\n          }\n        });\n      });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests so far**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run src/tests/routes.test.ts src/tests/documents.test.ts src/tests/ot.test.ts\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 3: Build check**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build 2>&1 | head -40\n```\nExpected: No errors\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/server.ts src/routes.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add Express server with WebSocket collaboration support\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: WebSocket Collaboration Tests (`src/tests/collab.test.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tests/collab.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Write collaboration tests**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport WebSocket from 'ws';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../server.js';\n\ntype ServerMsg = { type: string; content?: string; version?: number; op?: unknown; message?: string };\n\nfunction connect(port: number, docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/documents/${docId}/ws`);\n    ws.once('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction nextMessage(ws: WebSocket): Promise<ServerMsg> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    ws.once('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        resolve(JSON.parse(data.toString()));\n      } catch (e) {\n        reject(e);\n      }\n    });\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction closeWs(ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    if (ws.readyState === WebSocket.CLOSED) { resolve(); return; }\n    ws.once('close', resolve);\n    ws.close();\n  });\n}\n\ndescribe('WebSocket collaboration', () => {\n  let server: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n  let port: number;\n  let docId: string;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    server = createApp(':memory:');\n    port = await server.start(0);\n    const res = await request(server.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Collab Doc', content: 'hello' });\n    docId = res.body.id;\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await server.stop();\n  });\n\n  it('sends sync message on connect', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    const msg = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('sync');\n    expect(msg.content).toBe('hello');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('returns error for nonexistent document', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, 'nonexistent-doc');\n    const msg = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('applies an insert operation and acks', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync = await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n    expect(sync.type).toBe('sync');\n\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'operation',\n      clientVersion: sync.version,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' },\n    }));\n\n    const ack = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // Verify via REST\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('hello world');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('broadcasts operation to other clients', async () => {\n    const ws1 = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws1); // sync\n\n    const ws2 = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'operation',\n      clientVersion: 0,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' },\n    }));\n\n    const ack = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    const broadcast = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(broadcast.type).toBe('operation');\n    expect((broadcast.op as { text?: string }).text).toBe('!');\n\n    await closeWs(ws1);\n    await closeWs(ws2);\n  });\n\n  it('converges concurrent edits from two clients', async () => {\n    // Start: \"hello\"\n    // Client A inserts \" world\" at pos 5 (version 0)\n    // Client B inserts \"!\" at pos 5 (version 0) - concurrent\n    // Expected after OT: \"hello world!\" or \"hello! world\" - both preserved\n    const ws1 = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync1 = await nextMessage(ws1);\n\n    const ws2 = await connect(port, docId);\n    const sync2 = await nextMessage(ws2);\n\n    // Both see version 0 \"hello\"\n    expect(sync1.version).toBe(sync2.version);\n\n    const opA = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' };\n    const opB = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' };\n\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: sync1.version, op: opA }));\n    const ackA = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(ackA.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // ws2 gets broadcast of opA\n    const broadcastA = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(broadcastA.type).toBe('operation');\n\n    // ws2 sends its op at old version - server will transform it\n    ws2.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: sync2.version, op: opB }));\n    const ackB = await nextMessage(ws2);\n    expect(ackB.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // ws1 gets broadcast of transformed opB\n    const broadcastB = await nextMessage(ws1);\n    expect(broadcastB.type).toBe('operation');\n\n    // Verify final content contains both edits\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    const finalContent = res.body.content as string;\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('world');\n    expect(finalContent).toContain('!');\n\n    await closeWs(ws1);\n    await closeWs(ws2);\n  });\n\n  it('rejects malformed operation (missing op fields)', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'operation', clientVersion: 0, op: { type: 'insert' } }));\n    const err = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('rejects invalid JSON', async () => {\n    const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n    await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    ws.send('not-json');\n    const err = await nextMessage(ws);\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    await closeWs(ws);\n  });\n\n  it('handles 10 concurrent clients without corruption', async () => {\n    const clients: WebSocket[] = [];\n    const N = 10;\n\n    for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n      const ws = await connect(port, docId);\n      await nextMessage(ws); // sync\n      clients.push(ws);\n    }\n\n    // Each client sends one insert\n    const sends = clients.map((ws, i) =>\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'operation',\n        clientVersion: 0,\n        op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: `${i}` },\n      }))\n    );\n\n    // Wait for all acks\n    const acks = await Promise.all(clients.map(nextMessage));\n    expect(acks.every((a) => a.type === 'ack')).toBe(true);\n\n    // Final content should contain all 10 digits\n    const res = await request(server.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    const content = res.body.content as string;\n    for (let i = 0; i < N; i++) {\n      expect(content).toContain(`${i}`);\n    }\n\n    await Promise.all(clients.map(closeWs));\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run\n```\nExpected: All pass\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nFix any lint errors found.\n\n**Step 4: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/tests/collab.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add WebSocket collaboration integration tests\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Lint Configuration Fix (if needed)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 7\n\nIf `npm run lint` fails due to missing ESLint config:\n\n**Step 1: Check for ESLint config**\n\n```bash\nls /workspace/.eslint*\n```\n\nIf no config exists, create `.eslintrc.cjs`:\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any': 'warn',\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n};\n```\n\n**Step 2: Re-run lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\n\n**Step 3: Commit if changes needed**\n\n```bash\ngit add .eslintrc.cjs\ngit commit -m \"chore: add ESLint configuration\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Final Verification\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint && npx vitest run\n```\n\nAll three must pass cleanly before the implementation is considered complete.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
